sentences: Christine Isobel Correa (born July 8, 1955) is an American jazz singer of Indian origin.
In 1979, she moved to the U.S. and attended the New England Conservatory of Music, where her teachers included Jaki Byard, Ran Blake, and Joe Maneri.
